smissed his works as sloppy and unfinished. But for others, they were fresh and exciting, filled with a sense of the sitter’s animated presence captured with energy and immediacy. Steven Nadler gives us the first full-length biography of Hals in many years and offers a view into seventeenth-century Haarlem and this culturally rich era of the Dutch Republic. He tells the story not only of Hals’s life, but also of the artistic, social, political, and religious worlds in which he lived and worked.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aPainterszNetherlandsvBiography. 0aPortrait painterszNetherlandsvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh  adutch golden age, vermeer, rembrandt, painters, baroque, biography, history, art, portraits, nonfiction, haarlem, 17th century, sitters, brush strokes, animation, descartes, catholicism, religion, st george militia company, career, independence, eighty years war, wealth, group portrait, realism, daylight, wedding, sheen, panels, color.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076650940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226698533423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226698533/original  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles